so, use the `useInsecureConnectionsForHost:` is right? If not, has any API or properties to set insecure?

@YioMidd if your server doesn't support SSL, then the code you pasted above is correct:

``` objective-c
[GRPCCall useInsecureConnectionsForHost:kHostAddress];
Connector *clientConnector = [Connector serviceWithHost:kHostAddress];
```

Make sure to call `useInsecureConnectionsForHost:kHostAddress` _before_ making any RPC to `kHostAddress` (because you don't want a secure connection to be opened by default).

I tried searching for the `"context canceled"` error message in the gRPC repository, but GitHub search can't find that message. I suspect it might come from the server. What language is your server written in, and what version of gRPC?

